<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/3283: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-01T12:00:00-04:00">July 1,
                                    1934—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>82. Your 124, June 30, 5 p.m. I should appreciate your sending a
                                series of frequent brief analytic telegrams during the current
                                German crisis.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>